## 3. System Overview

This document records the JUnit testing completed within the Academi Gymraeg application. The tests were created under the `src/test/java` directory and were executed using Eclipse with **Run As > JUnit Test**.

The application test checked that the Spring Boot application context loaded correctly and that selected application beans were available. The controller tests checked that selected controller classes were detected and created successfully by the Spring application context. The LoginUser controller was also tested to confirm that the login method returned the expected login view name.

The model tests checked that selected model classes stored and returned field values correctly through getter and setter methods. The tests also checked enum values, default values, and simple object relationships, such as adding a question to a test and confirming that the question referenced the same test.

The repository tests checked that selected repository interfaces were detected and created successfully by the Spring application context. These tests confirmed that the repository beans were available for dependency injection. Repository query result testing was not included because that would require controlled test data or a separate test database configuration.

The security tests checked that selected security classes were created successfully. This included checking that the first user configuration component and user details component were available through the Spring application context, and that the login success handler object could be created.

The service tests checked that selected service classes were created successfully by the Spring application context. These tests confirmed that the main service beans were available and could be injected where required. Detailed service method behaviour testing was not included in this version.

