**Summary Notes:**  
JUnit testing confirmed that the Spring Boot application context loaded successfully and that selected application beans were available. The controller package tests confirmed that the selected controller classes were created successfully by the Spring application context. The LoginUser controller was also tested to confirm that the login method returned the expected `login` view name.

Model package testing confirmed that the selected model classes stored and returned field values correctly through getter and setter methods. The tests also confirmed enum values, default values, and simple object relationships, including the relationship between Tests and Questions objects.

Repository package testing confirmed that the selected repository interfaces were created successfully by the Spring application context and were available for dependency injection. These tests did not check live query results or database content.

Security package testing confirmed that the selected security classes could be created successfully. The tests checked that the first user configuration component and user details component were available through the Spring application context, and that the login success handler object could be created.

Service package testing confirmed that the selected service classes and configuration class were created successfully by the Spring application context and were available for dependency injection. These tests did not check detailed service method behaviour or database result accuracy.

